        {
            "name": "Crocodile",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "Crocodiles can be found basking on riverbanks, lurking in swamps, or floating in lakes. They are usually are indistinguishable from logs when viewed from afar\u2014at least until they attack. Alligators have similar statistics, but because they often live in more temperate climates, they endure cold temperatures better. Unlike alligators, crocodiles can tolerate salt water. Both are formidable predators that are likely to devour careless adventurers who fail to watch where they step.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 16",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 67
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Crocodile",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Crocodile Locations",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Crocodiles often live in warm, tropical areas, either in fresh or salt water. Alligators are found in more varied climates, but only in fresh water. Deinosuchuses, particularly the largest and most dangerous of their kind, prefer estuaries, bays, or other brackish bodies of water connected to both river and sea.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 67
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Crocodile Resources",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "A crocodile\u2019s skin can be used as leather, and its meat is chewy and mild, though even a large crocodile doesn\u2019t usually yield more than 50 pounds of usable meat.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 67
                    },
                    "subtype": "treasure_and_rewards",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
                    "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Powerful and primeval in appearance, crocodiles are dangerous natural predators that dwell in marshes, riverbeds, swamps, and other wetlands.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 67
            }
